  <steps>
    <step num="0">Salt and pepper chicken. </step>
    <step num="1">In a large pot, brown chicken in olive oil. Remove chicken and set aside. </step>
    <step num="2">In the same pot, add garlic, ginger, jalapeños and onions. Cook until translucent. </step>
    <step num="3">Pour in the tomato puree, unsweetened coconut milk and chicken broth. </step>
    <step num="4">Add the chicken back to the pot. Bring to a simmer. Cover and cook for 45 - 60 minutes. </step>
    <step num="5">Serve with rice. Garnish with cilantro or parsley. </step>
    <step num="6">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
